\@writefile{lof}{\contentsline {figure}{\numberline {4}{\ignorespaces PI-GNODE predictions on the four test events with the most fire pixels. Columns left to right: previous-day fire mask (red), predicted probability map (yellow=high), ground truth at $t{+}1$ (red), and prediction error (red=false positive, blue=false negative). The model correctly localizes spread to previously-burning regions plus a narrow expansion zone, but consistently under-predicts the magnitude of fast spread events.}}{6}{figure.caption.13}\protected@file@percent }
\newlabel{fig:qual}{{4}{6}{PI-GNODE predictions on the four test events with the most fire pixels. Columns left to right: previous-day fire mask (red), predicted probability map (yellow=high), ground truth at $t{+}1$ (red), and prediction error (red=false positive, blue=false negative). The model correctly localizes spread to previously-burning regions plus a narrow expansion zone, but consistently under-predicts the magnitude of fast spread events}{figure.caption.13}{}}
